		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-0dccb3f8-7fff-076c-ea1d-e221db11a6d4\" dir=\"ltr\">Your extensive time under the burden of your bonded artifact has given you an unusually good sense for curse magic. You can perform a one-hour ritual over a magic item and then make a Charisma check with a DC of 7 for a common item, 10 for an uncommon item, 13 for a rare item, 16 for a rare item, or 19 for a legendary item, adding your proficiency bonus to the roll. You cannot use this feature on artifacts. On a success, you learn whether the item is cursed or not. On a failure, you are unable to untangle the item&rsquo;s magic and learn nothing (but are aware of the failure). You can try again with the same item, but must wait a week between attempts.&nbsp;</p>",
